# Supply-chain hardening (SEC #32)
#
# ignore-scripts=true: blocks lifecycle hooks (preinstall, install, postinstall,
# prepare, …) from running during `npm install`. Arbitrary install-time code
# execution is the primary vector for malicious npm packages.
# CI and local development work fine without scripts; any intentional
# build/codegen runs are driven by explicit `npm run <script>` invocations.
#
# registry: pins all installs to the official npm registry. Prevents
# dependency-confusion attacks where a private package name is shadowed by a
# malicious public package on an alternate registry.
#
# Note: git:// and github: URL specifiers are blocked at the lockfile level —
# `lockfile-lint` (run in pretest / CI) rejects any entry that does not
# resolve through https://registry.npmjs.org/. There is no `allow-git` option
# in npm itself; the protection is provided by the lockfile audit.

ignore-scripts=true
registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
